Alembic migrations for the Wasool backend
==========================================

The DB URL is resolved at runtime from the DATABASE_URL env var (see env.py);
credentials are never stored in alembic.ini. With DATABASE_URL unset it falls
back to the local SQLite dev DB.

Commands (run from the backend/ directory):

  # Apply all migrations (fresh database — e.g. a new environment or CI):
  alembic upgrade head

  # Create a new migration after changing models in models/tables.py:
  alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"

  # Inspect status:
  alembic current
  alembic history

ONE-TIME ADOPTION ON AN EXISTING DATABASE
-----------------------------------------
Production and the dev DB were created by the legacy init_db()/run_migrations()
startup code and already contain the full schema, but have no alembic_version
row. Do NOT run `alembic upgrade head` against them (it would try to recreate
existing tables). Instead, mark the baseline as already applied:

  alembic stamp head

After stamping, all future schema changes go through Alembic migrations.

NOTE: startup DDL in models/database.py (init_db/run_migrations) is still active
and idempotent for now; retiring it in favor of an `alembic upgrade head`
release step is a Phase B task. Until then, treat models/tables.py as the source
of truth and keep new migrations in sync with it.
